CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 7, 1951, pg. 9 reads: "Toujours Amies - One of this town's newest youngset clubs, sponsored by Mrs. Frances Nunn and Vivian Mason, made its debut at a dance given at Carney Post Wednesday night. These popular teen-agers include, first row, left to right: Miss Mason, co-sponsor; Norma Lee and Germaine Lee.  Second row: Cleo Whitaker, Mrs. Nunn. Helen West, Gwendolyn Sheffey, Sylvia Kemp, Annie Mell Woods, Elva Lee, Sandra Williams and Dorothy Lovelace. Insets, left, Vivian Griffle and right, Barbara Ashby.  The girls will be featured in forthcoming Delta Jabberwock, April 20. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Toujours Amies club members, first row: Vivian Mason, Norma Lee, and Germaine Lee; second row: Cleo Whitaker, Frances Nunn, Helen West, Gwendolyn Sheffey, Sylvia Kemp, Annie Mell Woods, Elva Lee, Sandra Williams, and Dorothy Lovelace, gathered around piano in domestic interior with oriental rug and scroll patterned curtains
